\[2b \cdot BD \cos B = BD^2 + a^2 - 8m^2.\]Then $4bm = BD = 29^3,$ so $b = 29^2/m.$  Also, $a^2 = 8m^2 + BD^2 - 2b \cdot BD \cos B$ becomes
\[a^2 = 8m^2 + 29^6/m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3 \cos B.\]We want to compute $\cos B.$

By the Law of Sines on triangle $ABC,$
\[\frac{a}{\sin A} = \frac{c}{\sin C},\]so
\[a = \frac{c \sin A}{\sin C}.\]Since $C = 90^\circ,$ $\sin C = 1,$ so $a = c \sin A.$  Then
\[a^2 = c^2 \sin^2 A = c^2 (1 - \cos^2 A).\]By the Pythagorean Theorem on triangle $ACD,$
\[AD = c \cos A.\]Then $c^2 = AD^2 + CD^2 = AD^2 + BC^2,$ so
\[a^2 = c^2 (1 - \cos^2 A) = (AD^2 + BC^2)(1 - \cos^2 A) = AD^2 + BC^2 \sin^2 A.\]Hence,
\[8m^2 + 29^6/m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3 \cos B = AD^2 + BC^2 \sin^2 A.\]By the Pythagorean Theorem on triangle $CBD,$ $BC^2 = c^2 - BD^2 = c^2 - 29^6.$  Also, $AD = c \cos A$ and $\sin^2 A = 1 - \cos^2 A,$ so
\[8m^2 + 29^6/m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3 \cos B = c^2 \cos^2 A + (c^2 - 29^6)(1 - \cos^2 A).\]Since $c^2 = AD^2 + BD^2 = AD^2 + 29^6,$ this simplifies to
\[8m^2 + 29^6/m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3 \cos B = AD^2 \cos^2 A + AD^2 - 29^6 \cos^2 A.\]By the Pythagorean Theorem on triangle $ACD,$ $AD^2 = c^2 - BC^2 = 2 \cdot 29^6 - c^2.$  Hence,
\[8m^2 + 29^6/m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3 \cos B = (2 \cdot 29^6 - c^2) \cos^2 A + 2 \cdot 29^6 - c^2.\]We know that $a^2 = c^2 (1 - \cos^2 A) = 8m^2 + 29^6/m^2,$ so $c^2 = a^2/(1 - \cos^2 A) = (8m^2 + 29^6/m^2)/(1 - \cos^2 A).$  Substituting, we get
\[8m^2 + 29^6/m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3 \cos B = (2 \cdot 29^6 - (8m^2 + 29^6/m^2)/(1 - \cos^2 A)) \cos^2 A + 2 \cdot 29^6 - (8m^2 + 29^6/m^2)/(1 - \cos^2 A)).\]Then
\[8m^2 + 29^6/m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3 \cos B = \frac{(2 \cdot 29^6 - 8m^2 - 29^6/m^2)(\cos^2 A - 1) + 2 \cdot 29^6}{\cos^2 A - 1}.\]Hence,
\[8m^2 + 29^6/m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3 \cos B = \frac{29^6(1 - \cos^2 A)(\cos^2 A - 1) + 2 \cdot 29^6(\cos^2 A - 1)}{(1 - \cos^2 A)(\cos^2 A - 1)}.\]Simplifying, we get
\[8m^2 + 29^6/m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3 \cos B = \frac{29^6 (1 - 2 \cos^2 A)}{(1 - \cos^2 A)(\cos^2 A - 1)}.\]Since $\cos^2 A + \sin^2 A = 1,$ $1 - \cos^2 A = \sin^2 A,$ and $\cos^2 A - 1 = -\sin^2 A,$ so
\[8m^2 + 29^6/m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3 \cos B = -\frac{29^6}{\sin^2 A - \cos^2 A} = -\frac{29^6}{\cos 2B}.\]Hence, $\cos B = -\frac{29^6}{2m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3}.$  Then
\begin{align*}
m + n &= 29^2 + 2m \\
&= 29^2 + 2 \cdot 29^2/\sqrt{2m^2 - 2 \cdot 29^3} \\
&= 29^2 + 2 \cdot 29^2/\sqrt{2 \cdot 29^6 - 2 \cdot 29^3} \\
&= 29^2 + 2 \cdot 29^2/\sqrt{2 \cdot 29^3(29^3 - 1)} \\
&= 29^2 + 2 \cdot 29^2/\sqrt{2 \cdot 29^3 \cdot 29^3} \\
&= 29^2 + 2 \cdot 29 \\
&= \boxed{1170}.
\end{align*}

