Since $PA$ and $PB$ are tangent to semicircles $SAR$ and $RBT$ at $A$ and $B,$ respectively, $O_1A = OP$ and $O_2B = OP.$  Hence, $O_1A = O_2B.$

Since arc $AS$ is $58^\circ$ and arc $BT$ is $37^\circ,$ $\angle AOR = 58^\circ$ and $\angle BOR = 37^\circ.$  Hence,
\[\angle APB = \angle APO + \angle BPO = (180^\circ - \angle AOR) + (180^\circ - \angle BOR) = \boxed{105^\circ}.\]

