Let the line through $P$ parallel to $RT$ intersect $AB$ at $Q.$  Then $\angle APQ = \angle ASR = 58^\circ,$ and $\angle BPQ = \angle BTR = 37^\circ.$  Furthermore, $\angle AQP = \angle RQS$ and $\angle PQB = \angle STB.$

